<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,289,458]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,289,314]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Comments.</emphasis>
Bravo (
<number box="[385,443,289,313]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2001.0">2001</number>
) proposed this subgenus to include species of 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1120,289,314]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[992,1120,289,314]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Trichomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with gonocoxites having a posteromedial lobe on which various bristles are inserted. This subgenus is currently known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1300,1389,326,349]" name="Panama" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,223,361,386]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
